==English==

===Etymology===
Historically (late [[Middle English]]) meant 'expel, drive out'. From Latin ''propellere'', meaning ''pro-'' 'forward' and ''pellere'' 'to drive'.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛl|-ɛl]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|propels|propelling|propelled|propelled}}

#To cause to [[move]], to [[surge]] [[forward]].

